ab displayed on the calculator.</p><h3><span id=3D"Step_2">Step 2</span></h=
3><p>Now input the value of the variable y in the block titled y.</p><h3><s=
pan id=3D"Step_3">Step 3</span></h3><p>Once you have added the value of x a=
nd y, enter the desired function regarding x in the blocks titled <b>Functi=
on with =E2=80=98x=E2=80=99 as a variable.</b></p><h3><span id=3D"Step_4">S=
tep 4</span></h3><p>Afterward, add the function concerning y in the block t=
itled <b>Function with =E2=80=98y=E2=80=99 as a variable.</b>&nbsp;The desi=
gn limitation of the calculator requires the function to be added concernin=
g both variables individually, as the calculator can deal with only one var=
iable at a time.</p><h3><span id=3D"Step_5">Step 5</span></h3><p>After fill=
ing all the desired information in the specified blocks, press the&nbsp;<b>=
Submit</b>&nbsp;button to calculate the slope of the secant line.</p><h3><s=
pan id=3D"Step_6">Step 6</span></h3><p>The result will appear on the calcul=
